    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-20T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-20T17:00:00-05:00" n="343"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d343">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/357</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-20T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 20, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7834. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 511. Referring further your No. 560, Embassy 10003, May 11, 5 p.m. In event
                    that Swedish agreement is concluded and you are authorized to adhere to it on
                    behalf of the War Trade Board, your adherence should take the form substantially
                    as set out in your cable above referred to, except that conclusion of adherence
                    should read as follows: “(1) are not required for consumption in United States
                    or in nations associated with United States in the war, or to meet other
                    obligation in United States; (2) will not directly or indirectly be exported to
                    any country or ally of any country with which the United States is or may be at
                    war so long as the above-mentioned agreement shall remain in force and be
                    observed by the Royal Swedish Government.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
